      "message": "All of this is replaced with SSL_get_verify_result above.\n\nThe callback was being called for every certificate in the chain, and it called this function, it was validating each cert and used the last one for creating UserSession.\n\nWithout callback, we don\u0027t have the intermediate object, instead, we have SSL* object, and we call SSL_get_verify_result to get the final result of the entire peer certificate verification, check https://docs.openssl.org/3.4/man1/openssl-verify/ and https://docs.openssl.org/3.4/man3/SSL_get_verify_result/#return-values",
